---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const updated = 'May 29, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Markdown Better View"
  description="Markdown Better View collects no data and includes no tracking. The app is sandboxed and the website uses no analytics or cookies."
>
  <Nav slot="nav" />
  <div class="wrap page">
    <div class="page-head">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="dated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Markdown Better View is built around a simple principle: your documents are
        yours. The app collects no personal data, contains no tracking or analytics,
        and never sends your files anywhere.
      </p>

      <h2>The app</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No data collection.</strong> The app does not collect, transmit, or
          sell any personal information.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No tracking.</strong> There are no analytics SDKs, advertising
          identifiers, or third-party trackers of any kind.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Sandboxed.</strong> The app runs in the macOS App Sandbox and can
          only access the files and folders you explicitly open or grant access to.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Stays on your Mac.</strong> Your documents are read locally and
          rendered on your device. Remote network requests are blocked, so opening a
          document never phones home.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Consistent with the app’s privacy manifest
        (<code>PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy</code>), the only declared API usage is reading
        file timestamps (to detect changes for live reload) and storing your
        preferences in macOS <code>UserDefaults</code> on your own device. Neither is
        used for tracking, and neither leaves your Mac.
      </p>

      <h2>This website</h2>
      <p>
        markdownbetterview.com uses no analytics, no cookies, and no third-party
        trackers. It is a static site served over HTTPS. We don’t know who visits or
        what they read.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email
        <a href="mailto:support@markdownbetterview.com">support@markdownbetterview.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
